===Pronunciation===
*floo͞t, /fluːt/, /flu:t/

===Noun===
'''flute''' (''plural'' [[flutes]])

#A [[woodwind]] instrument consisting of a [[metal]], [[wood]] or [[bamboo]] tube with a row of circular holes and played by blowing across a hole in the side of one end or through a narrow channel at one end against a sharp edge, while covering none, some or all of the holes with the fingers to vary the note played.
#A [[glass]] with a long, narrow [[bowl]]and a long stem, used for drinking [[wine]], especially [[champagne]]. <!--Note: "bowl" is the correct term to use here - confirmed at http://66.102.9.104/search?q=cache:N9GMnphl-vcJ:www.daacs.org/aboutDatabase/pdf/cataloging/Glass.pdf+%22parts+of+a+glass%22+stem&hl=en -->

